  "text": "Because hepatic ALOXE3 expression enhanced peripheral insulin sensitivity in HTFC-fed mice (Fig.4) , and because PPARg agonism by TZDs enhances peripheral insulin sensitivity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , we evaluated whether ALOXE3 enhances peripheral insulin and glucose homeostasis dependent on PPARg and yet independent of the leptin receptor. Fasting circulating insulin and HOMA-IR were significantly lower in ALOXE3 db/db mice without changes in circulating glucose when compared with db/db mice expressing GFP. The reduction in circulating insulin and HOMA-IR were reversed in mice concomitantly treated with the PPARg inhibitor, GW9662, suggesting that ALOXE3 improves glucose and insulin homeostasis in a PPARg-dependent. In contrast with our dietinduced model, targeted hepatic ALOXE3 expression did not reduce circulating lipids in leptin receptor-deficient mice. Together, the data in our leptin-deficient model elucidate leptin-and PPARg-dependent functions by ALOXE3.",
